# SKILL_AEC_KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH — AEC Knowledge Graph

> **Purpose:** The AEC Knowledge Graph (AEC-KG) is the single structure that connects
> every artifact the pipeline produces — documents, scope items, RFIs, submittals,
> trades, spec sections, drawings, personnel, and GIS features — into a traversable
> graph. Flat JSON registers answer "what are all the FATAL RFIs?" A knowledge graph
> answers "which trades are blocked by open FATAL RFIs whose source documents are
> superseded, and what submittals are still pending for those trades?"
>
> **Integration point:**
> ```
> SKILL_AEC_DOCUMENT_CORPUS   → document nodes + family edges
> SKILL_AEC_SCOPE_EXTRACTION  → scope item nodes + evidence edges
> SKILL_AEC_RFI_SUBMITTAL     → RFI/submittal nodes + blocking edges
> SKILL_GIS_GEOSPATIAL        → site feature nodes + spatial edges
> SKILL_OPENAPI_SPEC          → API contract for graph query endpoints
> SKILL_DATABASE_ONTOLOGY_EXPORT → RDF/OWL export of the graph
> ```

