## Graph Data Model

The AEC-KG uses a **labeled property graph** model: every node and every edge carries
a type label and a dictionary of properties. Both NetworkX and Neo4j implement this
model natively.

### Node Taxonomy

| Node Type | Label | Key Property | Description |
|-----------|-------|-------------|-------------|
| Document | `Document` | `doc_id` | Any corpus artifact (addendum, RFI, spec, drawing, geotech) |
| Scope Item | `ScopeItem` | `item_id` | Extracted scope item from SKILL_AEC_SCOPE_EXTRACTION |
| RFI | `RFI` | `rfi_number` | Request for Information record |
| Submittal | `Submittal` | `submittal_number` | Submittal record (shop drawing, product data, etc.) |
| Trade | `Trade` | `name` | Construction trade (Structural, MEP, Enclosure, Civil, …) |
| SpecSection | `SpecSection` | `section_number` | CSI MasterFormat section, e.g. "03 30 00" |
| Drawing | `Drawing` | `drawing_number` | Individual drawing sheet, e.g. "S2.1", "A-101" |
| Person | `Person` | `name` | Any named party (GC, design team, reviewer) |
| Organization | `Organization` | `name` | Firm-level entity (GC, AOR, Structural EOR, …) |
| Zone | `Zone` | `zone_id` | Spatial zone or phase area |
| GISFeature | `GISFeature` | `feature_id` | Site boundary, utility corridor, control point |
| Conflict | `Conflict` | `conflict_id` | Detected contradiction between two document nodes |
| Assumption | `Assumption` | `assumption_id` | Priced assumption tied to an unanswered question |

### Relationship (Edge) Taxonomy

| Edge Type | From → To | Properties | Meaning |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|---------|
| `EXTRACTED_FROM` | ScopeItem → Document | `confidence`, `page`, `anchor_text` | Scope item sourced from document |
| `CONTRADICTS` | Document → Document | `conflict_id`, `field`, `value_a`, `value_b` | Two documents give conflicting values |
| `SUPERSEDES` | Document → Document | `issue_date` | Addendum or revision supersedes earlier document |
| `REFERENCES` | ScopeItem → Drawing | `sheet`, `detail` | Scope item references a drawing |
| `GOVERNED_BY` | ScopeItem → SpecSection | `section_number` | Scope item falls under a spec section |
| `BELONGS_TO` | ScopeItem → Trade | — | Trade ownership of scope item |
| `BLOCKS` | RFI → ScopeItem | `priority`, `since_date` | Open RFI prevents pricing of scope item |
| `GENERATED_BY` | RFI → Conflict | — | Conflict detection created this RFI |
| `REQUIRES` | SpecSection → Submittal | `lead_days`, `submittal_type` | Spec section mandates a submittal |
| `COVERS` | Submittal → ScopeItem | — | Submittal covers the scope item |
| `ISSUED_BY` | RFI → Person | `role` | Party who issued the RFI |
| `ISSUED_TO` | RFI → Person | `role` | Party who must answer the RFI |
| `EMPLOYED_BY` | Person → Organization | `role` | Org relationship |
| `LOCATED_IN` | ScopeItem → Zone | `confidence` | Scope item located in spatial zone |
| `CORRESPONDS_TO` | ScopeItem → GISFeature | `distance_m` | Scope item linked to a GIS feature |
| `ANSWERS` | Document → RFI | `date`, `disposition` | A document (addendum, response letter) answers an RFI |
| `DEPENDS_ON` | ScopeItem → ScopeItem | `dependency_type` | Scope item cannot price without another |

### Property Constraints

```
Every node MUST have:
  - node_type    : str   (matches label)
  - node_id      : str   (globally unique — use {type_prefix}:{key})
  - created_at   : str   (ISO datetime)
  - project_id   : str   (project scoping)

Every edge MUST have:
  - rel_type     : str   (matches relationship label)
  - created_at   : str
  - source       : str   (script or session that created this edge)

Recommended on most edges:
  - confidence   : float (0.0–1.0)
  - evidence     : str   (quote or pointer supporting the relationship)
```

### Node ID Convention

```
Format:  {TYPE_PREFIX}:{KEY}
Examples:
  DOC:ADD-003          — Document, addendum 003
  SCOPE:STRUCT-042     — Scope item, structural, sequence 42
  RFI:RFI-017          — RFI 017
  SUB:SUB-0042         — Submittal 0042
  TRADE:Structural     — Trade node
  SPEC:03.30.00        — Spec section (dots, not spaces, for IDs)
  DWG:S2.1             — Drawing sheet
  ZONE:LEVEL-03-NORTH  — Zone
  GIS:UTIL-CORRIDOR-01 — GIS feature
  PERSON:J.Smith.GC    — Person (disambiguate by org suffix)
  ORG:AcmeCorp         — Organization
  CONFLICT:CONF-001    — Conflict record
```

