## Common Issues & Fixes

| Issue | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `KeyError` on `add_edge` | Node not yet added before edge | Always add both endpoint nodes before adding the edge; use `populate_from_pipeline_registers()` which handles ordering |
| Cypher `MATCH` returns 0 rows | Node label mismatch (`ScopeItem` vs `Scope_Item`) | Enforce exact label strings from taxonomy; use `create_schema_constraints()` to lock labels |
| `betweenness_centrality` hangs | Graph too large (>5,000 nodes) | Use `k=500` approximation parameter |
| GraphML export fails on list values | NetworkX GraphML serializer cannot handle Python lists | Convert list attributes to JSON strings before export: `json.dumps(value)` |
| Duplicate edges between same pair | `MultiDiGraph` allows this | Expected and correct; use `key` parameter to distinguish parallel edges |
| RFI blocks scope item not found in KG | Scope baseline and RFI log are out of sync | Run corpus extraction and scope extraction in same session before populating KG |
| `SUPERSEDES` chain wrong direction | Newer doc should point TO older doc | `SUPERSEDES` edge direction: `newer_doc → older_doc`; confirm with `kg.edges_of_type("SUPERSEDES")` |
| Neo4j `MERGE` creates duplicate nodes | Key property differs by whitespace or case | Normalize all IDs to stripped, lowercase before ingestion |
| Cytoscape render is unreadable | Too many nodes (>500) in one render | Export a `extract_trade_subgraph()` or `extract_rfi_neighbourhood()` instead of full graph |
| RDF export fails validation | URI contains illegal characters (spaces, colons in IDs) | Apply `uri()` sanitization function; replace `:`, spaces, and `/` with `_` |

